Synopsis:
   on [<modes>]names [<serial#>] [-|^]<match> { <action> }

Description:
   This hook is triggered whenever the client receives server output from
   the NAMES command on join to a channel, or when a scan(2) command
   is performed.

Parameters:
   $0    count

   The following is repeated for count users.
   $1    nicknames of (visible) users on the channel
   $2    speed
   $3    shared files

See Also:
   scan(2); names(2); set show_channel_names

Other Notes:
   This hook is not triggered by the NAMES commands.

